title: Democrats Hold the Senate, as Cortez Masto Ekes Out a Victory in Nevada
description: Senator Catherine Cortez Masto defeated Adam Laxalt, the state’s former attorney general. Democrats now will try to add to their control of the chamber in Georgia’s runoff election on Dec. 6.
dc:creator: Jonathan Weisman
media:credit: Mikayla Whitmore for The New York Times
media:description: Senator Catherine Cortez Masto at her election night party in Las Vegas. Days later, her victory over Adam Laxalt, a Republican former attorney general of Nevada, was confirmed.
